The duration of follow-up was not specified in most studies and there was a lack of studies on the long-term supports for HCWs post-epidemic. While others emphasised the need for prompt and continuous psychiatric interventions in high mortality infectious disease outbreaks (
 Lee et al., 2018; 
 Wang et al., 2020; 
 Pouralizadeh et al., 2020; 
 Li et al., 2020c). Imminent utilisation of interventions promoting wellbeing for HCWs facing COVID-19 was suggested for frontline workers, females and nurses (
 Lai et al., 2020).
